reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 6, 2017
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Voice Turn by Turn Directions for Safety
reviews.reviewText: The Garmin system I purchased is a refurbished one. It is easily programmed for directions and the turn by turn voice directions allows eyes on the road safety. My only concern would be the suction mount which fell from the window where I mounted it, during my drive. But the unit never stopped functioning.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 26, 2017
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars good product at a good price
reviews.reviewText: After charging and loading the maps from the Garmin web site, the unit powered on and worked as advertised.With a high speed connection, it took over an hour to load, so it may be a challenge for those with a slow connection to the Internet.I could not tell it was refurbished, as it looked and performed like a new one, but at a much better price.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 14, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars A few hiccups...
reviews.reviewText: The provided cord to run from the USB port on my computer to the Garmin Nuvi 55 I purchased did not work. Good news that I had an old cord from the Garmin this purchase was replacing and that did work to register and update the device. Also, I needed to get a micro SD card to allow the refurbished Nuvi to hold more than one set of regional maps.If you are planning a far drive, Say from Florida to Yellowstone, or my last years vacation from Alabama, US to Newfoundland, CA you Will need to augment the onboard data capacity. But as I said I used one of these last year with the added micro sd card and aside from getting a bit glitchy within 2 kilometers of the farthest northeastern coast of Newfoundland I liked it well enough to replace it when the first got broken.One additional advantage was to adjust the display to show our speed / progress in kilometers on entering Canada. If you have a US automobile it can be a royal pain to use the itty bitty markings on your speedometer to determine if you are exceeding the Canadian speed limits.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 15, 2016
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Updating the map from my computer was very easy and fast
reviews.reviewText: My GPS is working well, but, it doesn't have the ability to find a street via zip code, just by city. Updating the map from my computer was very easy and fast.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 4, 2018
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Easy to use, priced well and feature packed.
reviews.reviewText: Excellent purpose-built GPS for those that drive for a living. Easy to use, easy to update, lifetime maps and very good accuracy. This beats the pants off Google or Bing Maps for easy of use and readability.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 30, 2016
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars He said it worked beautifully -- and was much more responsive than our older ...
reviews.reviewText: We have an older version, but bought this for our son as he drove across country for his first military assignment. He said it worked beautifully -- and was much more responsive than our older model ( although we still love and use that). Being yet, he's presumed he'd just use his cell phone doe GPS services, but was glad to keep his phone open for music and other uses, and that the Garmin worked well even whe he was out of cell range. A worthy purchase.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 7, 2017
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Accurate and easy to use!
reviews.reviewText: So far used it for my trip to Colorado, Wyoming, Montana, Missouri, Arkansas and Texas. Update my Garmin monthly for road changes. With pretty much pin point accuracy, I love this GPS!!!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 19, 2021
reviews.reviewText: It doesn't give you the right directions until the very last min. Takes you the long way to Grandma's house . Can't seem to put my address into GPS to go home option.
